# ------------------------------- start WAF introduciton ------------------------------- # 
    ==> Quick view: WAF works on 2 different modes:
                        - passive mode.
                        - reactive mode (blocking mode).
                    
                    regex is the main method to define the rules of how WAF should behave.
                    
                    Whitelisting mode is the best solution to protect a web application; on the other hand, to customize the rules
                    is not an easy task. further more, the Whitelisting mode is prone to false positivies, which is the reason it is very
                    common to find WAFs deployed in blacklisting mode rather than Whitelisting mode.
# -------------------------------   end WAF introduciton ------------------------------- # 


# ------------------------------- start WAF enumeration ------------------------------- # 
    # ---------- start techniques ---------- #
        - Cookie.
        - Response header.
        - Response server information header.
        - Response body.
        - Blocking message.
    
    # ---------- |Tools| ---------- #
        - wafw00f: https://code.google.com/p/waffit/
        - nmap: http-waf-fingerprint script
        - imperva-detect: https://code.google.com/p/imperva-detect/
    
# -------------------------------   end WAF enumeration ------------------------------- # 